I will make just about anything with fresh ginger in it. I've made it twice, as the recipe reads, and I wouldn't change a thing. I used it first on a carrot cake, and then on carrot cake cupcakes. My friend's husband at three in a row, and all the leftover frosting. Enough said.

Rating: 4
Mmmm! I cut back the sugar to 2 cups and upped the fresh ginger by maybe a teaspoon. Light but rich consistency, just sweet enough, and buoyed by the subtle aromatic flavor of the ginger mixed with the tang of the cream cheese. As others have written, it's much more than is needed for a dozen carrot cupcakes; probably half the icing remained when had finished.

Rating: 4
This is one of my favorite icing recipes I have made. I put it once on devil's food cupcakes and once on green tea cupcakes (inspired by Japan during the Cherry Blossom Festival). You can vary the amount of ginger depending on what you are paring it with. I don't like super heavy frosting where all I can taste is the butter and the feel of my mid section expanding. This frosting it absolutely amazing and it not heavy.

