Rating: 2
Made this as directed and was not impressed. It just didn't have the gingery flavor I was looking for. So, I took it back to my mixer, added a tsp of vanilla, minced up 1/3 cup of crystalized ginger, a couple Tbls of buttermilk and 1 Tbls of cinnamon. These changes made it really tasty. Next time, I'll sprinkle the minced crystalized ginger on the outside, instead of mixing it in.

Rating: 3
I used 2- 8oz. pkgs. of cream cheese, the suggested amount of butter and about a cup of sugar. I doubled the ginger and also added grated orange peel and some cinnamon. The result was a delicious, spicy icing (just the right amount of sweetness) that was fabulous on carrot cake. I topped it with grated dark chocolate and a little more grated orange peel. My guests (age 9 and up) gave it rave reviews!

